The senior administration official gave a preview of day one of the G20 summit, highlighting President Biden's meetings with Pope Francis, Italian President Mattarella, Italian Prime Minister Draghi, and French President Macron. The official emphasized the United States' commitment to its allies and face-to-face diplomacy. The first plenary session of the G20 will focus on the global economy and the global pandemic, with leaders endorsing the establishment of a global minimum tax to ensure fair taxation for corporations. The official also mentioned the need to address imbalances in global energy markets and the importance of global energy supplies keeping up with demand. The official did not provide specific targets for energy production or discuss accountability for vaccine sharing, but highlighted the United States' efforts in donating vaccines and brokering agreements for African countries. The briefing was held on background and under embargo until the following morning.